channel.title: Eclipse - Unable to Run Server
channel.description: Can't run this fucking shit in Eclipse, please help. I have the project directed to my server/source and when I press run it says unable to launch - can not be launched, there are no recent launches. What do I do? Is it targeted wrong? Do I need to direct it somewhere else? The Server Java file I have opened and tried to run as well, but that doesn't do anything. Am I not importing it right or something? I haven't had problems like this on BlueJ so I don't know what the issue is.

item.title: Eclipse - Unable to Run Server
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

EJ:

How do I re add it? And thank you so much for your help so far

Click the “Server” project on eclipse. Press delete. Make sure to not delete the files from your computer.

Go to file > new > java project.
Type a name for the project.
Then, change the path for the project to your folder with the src/bin/data/etc folders.
Press the ‘next’ button, it should generate your project.
Verify it’s set up correctly, then hit finish

item.description:
@X-J-K-X wrote:

You’re not opening an eclipse project as it’s missing the files that are generated when you create a new ‘eclipse project’

Create a new eclipse project, then copy your folders to the project destination. I don’t use eclipse but the same applies with netbeans. I don’t think you can just open your folder and expect it to run.
